Quark 04-Jan-19 12:29 AM
you can get it from the modifier
although a modifier has two things
a caster and a parent
parent is the unit that the modifier is on
and caster is the unit that applied modifier
sometimes, like in your case, parent and caster are the same thing
because you did something like
parent:AddNewModifier(caster, ...)
so what you probably want to do is
self:GetParent():Heal(healing, nil)
self refers back to the modifier
GetParent() is a function on the modifier that gets the unit that the modifier is currently on
and from there you call Heal on that unit
